# Toronto Rising — synchronization conventions

## Core contract

- Treat `gameState` as the single source of truth.
- Keep **mutation** and **reconciliation** separate:
  - Mutation writes state (`S.setStateVal`, `S.setPlayerVal`, module mutation APIs).
  - Reconciliation applies world changes (`UI`, lights, sound, spawned objects).
- After a relevant mutation, call an explicit sync entry point (`Sync.player(color)`, `Sync.full()`, or domain reconcile function where appropriate).
- Do not hide side effects in state setters.

## World application authority (emitters, lights, spawns)

`gameState` is the single authority for **intent**. **Physical** updates (AssetBundle audio, `L.SetLightMode`, spawns, staggered `Wait.time` fades) must not be driven twice for the same steady-state intent in one flow—typically **eager domain setters** plus **`Sync.full` → `reconcileFromState`** on the same slice.

When a mutation path **already** applied emitters/lights to match persisted state, either:

- route that slice **only** through the domain reconciler (preferred for new code), or
- call the domain’s **fingerprint prime** after eager apply (e.g. `Soundscape.markReconciledToCurrentState`) so incremental `reconcileFromState` does not stack a second fade, or
- call **`invalidateReconcileCache`** only when the world may be **out of sync** with state and the next `Sync.full` must re-apply.

Survey notes: [`.dev/Sychronizing Game Functionality/Dual_apply_survey.md`](.dev/Sychronizing%20Game%20Functionality/Dual_apply_survey.md).

## Reconciler rules

- Reconciler functions must be idempotent.
- Reconciler functions must read state and apply only required diffs.
- Reconciler functions must not write back into state except for narrowly-scoped runtime context flags that are part of the sync model (for example per-player rolling context).
- Prefer naming in the form:
  - `reconcileForPlayer(color)`
  - `reconcileAllPlayers()`
  - `reconcileFromState()`

## Lighting-specific rules

- Derive desired player light mode from current state priority, not restore stacks.
- Current player-light priority is:
  - `ROLLING` > `NPC-role exception (when implemented)` > `absent from seat layout` > `HUNGRY` > scene seat preset / `STANDARD`
- Collapse seat-layout absence to `OFF`. Scene darkness is explicit in `C.LightModes.*.spotlights`, not inferred from preset key suffix.
- Do not reintroduce `modeRestore`-style push/pop state.

## Multiplayer host authority (until TOR-144 E2E passes)

> **⚠ PREMISE UNDER ACTIVE CORRECTION (2026-07-04):** This section's host-**execution** mandates assume TTS runs handlers on every client. That premise is contradicted by the authoritative TTS model (**Lua runs on the host only**). See [`Execution Model Correction — Remediation Plan`](../../.dev/Multiplayer%20Functionality/Execution%20Model%20Correction%20%E2%80%94%20Remediation%20Plan.md). **For new code: do NOT add `U.requireHostForWorldMutation` / `U.isHostClient()` execution guards; do NOT ad-hoc remove existing ones (staged in the plan).** The **`U.isStorytellerSteamPlayer` actor-identity** guidance below remains correct.

Solo Host development **does not** validate fan-out or join-client paths. Apply on **every** new handler, chunk-load hook, object script, and `Global.*` mutator:

- **Tier C (world I/O)** — Host client only: `U.requireHostForWorldMutation(context)` (also at **Global chunk load**, not only `onLoad` / `onObjectDrop`).
- **Who acted vs who executes** — `U.isStorytellerSteamPlayer` ≠ host-only; steam gate alone fails on fan-out when the Storyteller drops objects.
- **Join-client PC Tier C** — `Global.call` → host-guarded Global callee; object scripts use bundle-safe gates, not `require("core.*")` for mutations.
- **Rolls** — do not host-guard entire `onObjectRandomize`; split Tier B (all clients) vs Tier C (`Sync.player` / lights on host).

Full policies P1–P10, pre-flight checklist, agent audit: [`.dev/Multiplayer Functionality/Preparing For Multiplayer.md`](../../.dev/Multiplayer%20Functionality/Preparing%20For%20Multiplayer.md). Always-on rule: [`.cursor/rules/toronto-rising-multiplayer-authority.mdc`](../../.cursor/rules/toronto-rising-multiplayer-authority.mdc). Authority model: [Bootstrap Authority](../../.dev/Sychronizing%20Game%20Functionality/Bootstrap%20Authority.md).

## Cleanup expectations

- Remove compatibility aliases once call sites are migrated.
- Remove comments that describe past migration steps; comments should describe current behavior.
- When sync APIs change, update `.dev/` docs in the same change.
